    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 9th level, if you are hidden from a creature when you cast a spell on it, the creature has disadvantage on any saving throw it makes against the spell this turn.</p>\n<p>Additionally, when you deal damage with a spell while hidden, you can roll half the bonus damage dice (rounded up) from your Sneak Attack feature, dealing the extra damage to one target of the spell. This counts as using your Sneak Attack feature for the turn.</p>",
